Professor Salim Abdool Karim has become a household name as the man in the know about the coronavirus. He is chairperson of the committee advising government on COVID-19. And he joins us now to tell us how we are doing as a country in our fight against the virus. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Professor Salim Abdool Karim says children are less susceptible to COVID-19 than adults. Karim says cases of Kawasaki diseases are rare. Kawasaki is an inflammatory syndrome associated with the coronavirus. WATCH: Professor Karim says COVID-19 here to stay for a while Karim says children should return to school, provided proper sanitation regulations are followed. READ: Benefits for children going back to school outweigh risks: expert But he warns that small outbreaks of infection should be expected at schools from time to time. Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga announced that Grade 7 and 12 will be the first group of learners to start learning on 1 June. Professor Salim Abdool Karim has become a household name as the man in the know about the coronavirus. He is chairperson of the committee advising government on COVID-19. And he joins us now to tell us how we are doing as a country in our fight against the virus. Courtesy #DStv403 - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.